t: Lord,*spn I cry out to You; Make*ld haste to me! Give*ld ear to my voice when I cry out to You.
Let*ld my prayer be set before You as*i incense, The*ld lifting up of my hands as*i the evening sacrifice.
Set*ln a guard, O Lord,*s over my mouth; Keep*ld watch over the door of my lips.
Do*ld not incline my heart to any evil thing, To*ld practice wicked works With*ld men who work iniquity; And*ld do not let me eat of their delicacies.

Let*ln the righteous strike me; It*ild shall*i be*i a kindness. And*ld let him rebuke me; It*ild shall*i be*i as excellent oil; Let*ld my head not refuse it. For*ln still my prayer is*i against the deeds of the wicked.
Their*ld judges are overthrown by the sides of the cliff, And*ld they hear my words, for they are sweet.
Our*ld bones are scattered at the mouth of the grave, As*ld when one plows and breaks up the earth.
But*ln my eyes are*i upon You, O God*s the Lord; In*ld You I take refuge; Do*ld not leave my soul destitute.
Keep*ld me from the snares they have laid for me, And*ld from the traps of the workers of iniquity.
Let*ld the wicked fall into their own nets, While*ld I escape safely.
